    <title>Install Softwares for High-energy Astronomy</title>
    <link href="https://blog.fxzheng.com/2015/10/18/high-energy-soft-install/"/>
    <id>https://blog.fxzheng.com/2015/10/18/high-energy-soft-install/</id>
    <published>2015-10-17T16:00:00.000Z</published>
    <updated>2016-05-01T19:24:27.793Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html">&lt;h1 id=&quot;DS9&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#DS9&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;DS9&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;DS9&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;Install&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Install&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Install&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Install&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;yaourt -S ds9-bin
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;Check-Installation&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Check-Installation&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Check Installation&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Check Installation&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Run DS9 by typing &lt;code&gt;ds9&lt;/code&gt; in your unix prompt&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&quot;HEASOFT&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#HEASOFT&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;HEASOFT&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;HEASOFT&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;Download-source-code&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Download-source-code&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Download source code&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Download source code&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Visit &lt;a href=&quot;http://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/docs/software/lheasoft/download.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;external&quot;&gt;http://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/docs/software/lheasoft/download.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;Unpack-the-file-to-the-installation-directory&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Unpack-the-file-to-the-installation-directory&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Unpack the file to the installation directory&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Unpack the file to the installation directory&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;cd /usr/local/
sudo tar zxvf /path/to/the/downloaded/file/heasoft-6.17src.tar.gz
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;Install-1&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Install-1&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Install&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Install&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;cd heasoft-6.17/BUILD_DIR
sudo ./configure
sudo make
sudo make install
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;this may take some time, so be patient : -) or you can have a coffee ~&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;Add-the-environment-variables&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Add-the-environment-variables&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Add the environment variables&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Add the environment variables&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Add following code to your ~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;export HEADAS=/usr/local/heasoft-6.17/(PLATFORM)
alias heainit=&amp;quot;. $HEADAS/headas-init.sh&amp;quot;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;where (PLATFORM) is a placeholder for the platform-specific string&lt;br&gt;denoting your machine’s architecture, for example: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu-libc2. 22&lt;br&gt;in my Archlinux&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;Check-installation&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Check-installation&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Check installation&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Check installation&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Run &lt;code&gt;heainit&lt;/code&gt; in your unix prompt&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&quot;XMM-SAS&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#XMM-SAS&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;XMM SAS&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;XMM SAS&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;Download&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Download&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Download&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Download&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt; Download from &lt;a href=&quot;http://xmm.esac.esa.int/sas/current/downloadandinstall.shtml&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;external&quot;&gt;http://xmm.esac.esa.int/sas/current/downloadandinstall.shtml&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;Unpack-it-to-the-installation-directory&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Unpack-it-to-the-installation-directory&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Unpack it to the installation directory&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Unpack it to the installation directory&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo mkdir /usr/local/SAS
cd /usr/local/SAS
sudo tar zxf /path/to/the/downloaded/file/sas_14.0.0-&amp;lt;OS&amp;gt;.tgz
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;Run-the-installation-file&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Run-the-installation-file&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Run the installation file&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Run the installation file&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo ./install.sh
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;Environment-settings&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Environment-settings&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Environment settings&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Environment settings&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Add following code to your ~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;alias sasinit=&amp;quot;. /usr/local/SAS/xmmsas_20141104_1833/setsas.sh&amp;quot;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;Check-installation-1&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Check-installation-1&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Check installation&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Check installation&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Run &lt;code&gt;sasinit&lt;/code&gt; in your unix prompt&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&quot;CALDB&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#CALDB&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;CALDB&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;CALDB&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;Download-1&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Download-1&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Download&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Download&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Chandra&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;  Visit &lt;a href=&quot;http://cxc.harvard.edu/ciao/download/caldb.html#caldb&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;external&quot;&gt;http://cxc.harvard.edu/ciao/download/caldb.html#caldb&lt;/a&gt; to download Chandra caldb&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Others&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;  Visit &lt;a href=&quot;http://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/docs/heasarc/caldb/caldb_supported_missions.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;external&quot;&gt;http://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/docs/heasarc/caldb/caldb_supported_missions.html&lt;/a&gt; to download&lt;br&gt;  caldb of missions needed such as Suzaku&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;Unpack-to-the-installation-directory&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Unpack-to-the-installation-directory&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Unpack to the installation directory&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Unpack to the installation directory&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;mkdir ~/caldb
cd ~/caldb
tar zxvf /path/to/the/downloaded/file/caldb_4.6.9_main.tar.gz
tar zxvf /path/to/the/downloaded/file/goodfiles_suzaku_xis_bcf_20151005.tar.gz
tar zxvf /path/to/the/downloaded/file/goodfiles_suzaku_xis_cpf_20151005.tar.gz
tar zxvf /path/to/the/downloaded/file/goodfiles_suzaku_xis_index_20151005.tar.gz
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;Environment-settings-1&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Environment-settings-1&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Environment settings&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Environment settings&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Add following code to your ~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;export CALDB=$HOME/caldb
export CALDBCONFIG=$CALDB/software/tools/caldb.config
export CALDBALIAS=$CALDB/software/tools/alias_config.fits
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h1 id=&quot;CIAO&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#CIAO&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;CIAO&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;CIAO&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;Before-installation&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Before-installation&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Before installation&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Before installation&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;link installed CALDB to your CIAO installation directory&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;ln -s ~/caldb ~/ciao-4.7/CALDB
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;Download-ciao-install-and-run-it&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Download-ciao-install-and-run-it&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Download ciao-install and run it&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Download ciao-install and run it&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Download from &lt;a href=&quot;http://cxc.harvard.edu/ciao/download/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;external&quot;&gt;http://cxc.harvard.edu/ciao/download/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;./ciao-install
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;just install ciao to your home directory : -)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;Install-dependences&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Install-dependences&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Install dependences&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Install dependences&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;yaourt -S libselinux
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;and more…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;Fix-a-bug&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Fix-a-bug&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Fix a bug&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Fix a bug&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;I got something like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;sh: symbol lookup error: sh: undefined symbol: rl_signal_event_hook
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;during installation, duckduckgoaround, I figured out following solution:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;cd ~/ciao-4.7/ots/lib/
mv libreadline.so.6 libreadline.so.6.bak
mv libreadline.so libreadline.so.bak
ln -s /usr/lib/libreadline.so.6.3 ~/ciao-4.7/ots/lib/libreadline.so.6
ln -s /usr/lib/libreadline.so.6 ~/ciao-4.7/ots/lib/libreadline.so
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;Environment-setting&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Environment-setting&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Environment setting&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Environment setting&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Add following code to your ~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;alias ciao=&amp;quot;source ~/ciao-4.7/bin/ciao.bash&amp;quot;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;Check-installation-2&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Check-installation-2&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Check installation&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Check installation&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;ciao
check_ciao_caldb
